Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1%small} (no need to peel!) into wedges
about the size of your index finger. Pop the wedges on a #baking tray{} and toss in a glug of
@olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Cook on the top shelf of
your oven until crispy at the edges and soft in the middle, about ~{30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Cut the
@vine tomatoes{1} into ½cm thick slices.

Add the @Cajun spice mix{1} to a splash of @olive oil{} in a #small bowl{} and mix together.
Cut the @halloumi{1} into 1cm thick slices. Rub the Cajun infused oil over the halloumi.

Put the @sour cream{1/2} in another small bowl and combine with a tiny bit of the garlic.
Add a pinch of salt and black pepper. Taste and add more garlic if you think it needs it.
Remove the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and finely slice (shred) widthways. Halve the
@brioche buns{2}.

When the wedges are ~{7%minutes} away from being ready, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high
heat. When the pan is hot, gently lay in the halloumi slices and cook until golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes} on each side, turning once. Remove the wedges from your oven.

Pop the brioche buns on a baking tray on the top shelf of your oven for ~{2%minutes}
(no more!) to crisp them up. Put a dollop of garlic sour cream on the bottom half of the
bun. Top with the tomato slices the halloumi and some lettuce (or whatever order you want!).
Finish with the top half of the bun. Serve the Cajun halloumi burgers with some sweet
potato wedges on the side. Enjoy!

> This super simple recipe is the thing veggie burger dreams are made of.